article.headline: Auburn 82, Buffalo 32
article.story:
AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Mandisa Stevenson had 16 points and eight
rebounds and No. 25 Auburn forced 23 steals Sunday in an 82-32
victory over Buffalo.

The Tigers (6-2) outscored Buffalo (1-3), controlling the inside
and converting 30 turnovers into 43 points.

Louise Emeagi had 14 points and four steals for Auburn while
Nitasha Brown added 12 points and Natasha Brackett 10. All 11
players scored for the Tigers.

Kim Kilpela led Buffalo with 13 points and nine rebounds but
shot just 4-for-13.

Auburn's suffocating defense offset an offense that sputtered at
times. Buffalo made just 4-of-21 field goals in the first half to
trail 35-11 and never got any closer, shooting 25 percent for the
game.
